  "texts": [
    "The adopted refined and not refined questions are reported in the replication package associated with this study.RQ3 examines the impact of employing different representations for the business process models within the BPLLM pipeline, as well as whether different embedding models affect our pipeline.",
    "In this direction, the natural text and the BPMN model representation for the Food Delivery process is evaluated as described in the previous RQs.",
    "For each process model representation, three different models are considered: all-MiniLM-L6-v2, bert-finetuned-bpmn, paraphrase-xlm-r-multilingual-v1.The first considered model is all-MiniLM-L6-v2foot_7 model, which projects sentences into a 384-dimensional dense vector space.Another model is bert-finetuned-bpmn 9.",
    "It is a fine-tuned version of bert-base-cased, trained on a dataset comprising textual process descriptions.",
    "Finally, the paraphrase-xlm-r-multilingual-v1foot_9 maps sentences to a 768dimensional dense vector space.RQ4 explores the effect of fine-tuning along with the use of RAG on the performance of the BPLLM."
  ],
